Comments: You can hear ManBearPig (from the LPU) sing on &#039;In The End&#039; at exactly 1:51 on the audio.

Show Notes:
- &#039;Petrified&#039; was over &#039;Points Of Authority&#039;. There was nothing over the outro.
- There was no intro for &#039;Breaking The Habit&#039;.
- Chester brought out a Canadian flag after &#039;Points Of Authority&#039; and hung it on Mike&#039;s keyboard before &#039;Numb&#039;.
- On the intro to &#039;Pushing Me Away (Piano Version)&#039;, the crowd started singing &#039;O Canada&#039; over Mike&#039;s keyboard part, so the band stopped and restarted the song. Afterwards, Mike commented, "That was like the remix".
- Joe added a few Leroy Jenkins samples in the set, throwing one in right after the outro to &#039;Points Of Authority&#039;, another before &#039;Leave Out All The Rest, and the last one on the outro to &#039;Faint&#039;. 

An LPLive.net release.
Enjoy.
Thanks to ManBearPig for the show.
